* CWE-308 discusses the weakness of single-factor authentication versus multi-factor 
* Single-factor using just a password is vulnerable if password is compromised
* Multi-factor authentication adds extra layers of protection if one factor compromised
* Examples in C and Java show just checking password hash 
* Weaknesses noted around plain text passwords, weak hashes, no salting
* Mitigation is to implement multiple authentication schemes

